Oh no... you mean literally extracting **every single** type, method, property, parameter, return type from a massive DLL, one by one? 😱

That's... actually what some legacy system migrations require. I've seen this with:
- Ancient COM components with no docs
- Proprietary vendor DLLs from companies that no longer exist
- "Enterprise" systems where the source code was lost years ago

If you really need to do this systematically:

```csharp
// At least make it less painful...
foreach (var type in assembly.GetTypes())
{
    File.AppendAllText("output.txt", $"\n\n===== {type.FullName} =====\n");

    foreach (var method in type.GetMethods())
    {
        // Output in a format you can process later
        File.AppendAllText("output.txt", 
            $"{method.ReturnType}|{method.Name}|{string.Join(",", method.GetParameters().Select(p => $"{p.ParameterType} {p.Name}"))}\n");
    }

    Thread.Sleep(10); // Don't lock up completely...
}
```

Then at least you have a text file you can search through instead of loading the DLL repeatedly.

